			<h2 class="author-name">John Jakes</h2>
			<div class="author-bio"><p>John Jakes is the acknowledged contemporary master of the family saga. He is the creator of the legendary eight-volume <em>Kent Family Chronicles</em>, the Main and Hazard families of <em>The North and South Trilogy</em>, and the Crowns of Chicago, German-Americans whose stories interweave the history of the twentieth century in <em>Homeland</em> and its sequel, <em>American Dreams</em>. His 2002 novel, <em>Charleston</em>, returned him to the turbulent years of the Revolution and the Civil War, and became his sixteenth consecutive <em>New York Times</em> bestseller.</p>
